Description:
Affinitas DMCC provides highly customized internationalization services for all organizations that are interested in developing a strong and profitable presence in the emerging markets with a special focus on United Arab Emirates & GCC.

We help clients step by step: from an initial tax advisory and commercial study to the implementation of the agreed upon, including the creation of the required legal structures to support their ventures.

We provide UAE compliant bookkeeping & accounting services. Our intimate knowledge of double taxation treaties enable us to optimize the tax burden of companies operating internationally.

Each Affinitas consultant has operated extensively, and successfully, within the emerging market economies and experienced first hand some of the typical challenges that new companies face whenever they approach a new territory: new legal environment, cultural challenges, hidden obstacles, political issues.

The organization has developed an extensive business and financial network at the private and governmental level in the following geographical areas: GCC, Caucasus, East Africa, Indian subcontinent and China. This network is made available to our clients and greatly facilitates their ability to succeed in the “emerging markets”.

Key Services:

- Advisory Services;
- Financial and Tax planning;
- Bookkeeping & Accounting (UAE)
- Business Set up;
- Commercial Agreements and cross-border transactions management;
- Feasibility Studies;

AIFI – Italian Private Equity, Venture Capital and Private Debt Association was founded in May 1986 and is internationally recognised for its activity of institutionally representing and promoting the private equity, venture capital and private debt activity in Italy. AIFI associates and represents financial institutions that professionally invest in companies and has developed a significant network of institutions, investors and professionals. 

In particular, the objectives AIFI wants to pursue are the following:

-	supporting and facilitating the development of private equity, venture capital and private debt activity in Italy and abroad;
-	working with institutional bodies to improve the legal environment of the private capital investment activity;
-	increasing awareness and understanding, within the Italian context, of the asset classes it represents;
-	supporting the constitution of qualified managerial groups both in associated companies and connected firms;
-	collecting and presenting information about the industry;
-	acting as interface and link to Italian and international financial players; 
-	creating a network between research centres, incubators, accelerators, universities and venture capitalists, in order to promote successful entrepreneurial ideas; 
-	maintaining ethical and professional standards in the private equity, venture capital and private debt industry.

Den Sociale Kapitalfond er professionel, specialiseret og værdidrevet udvikler og forvalter af investeringsfonde, der kombinerer attraktive finansielle afkast med målbar social effekt til gavn for udsatte grupper i samfundet. 

Den Sociale Kapitalfond forvalter i dag følgende fonde for danske og internationale professionelle investorer:

- Den Sociale Kapitalfond Invest: Kapitalfonde målrettet socialt ansvarlige mindre og mellemstore virksomheder;
- Den Sociale Kapitalfond Effekt: Investeringsfonde for offentlig-private partnerskaber der skaber positive sociale effekter;
- Den erhvervsdrivende fond, Den Sociale Kapitalfond: Laboratorium og tænketank for sociale impact investeringer. 

Den Sociale Kapitalfond blev etableret i 2011 af Lars Jannick Johansen og TrygFonden og er en skandinavisk pioner inden for sociale impact investeringer. 

---

Den Sociale Kapitalfond (litt. “The Social Capital Fund") is a professional, specialized, and value-driven developer and manager of investment funds that combine attractive financial returns with measurable social impact for the benefit of vulnerable groups in society.

Today, Den Sociale Kapitalfond manages the following funds for Danish and international professional investors:

- Den Sociale Kapitalfond Invest: Private equity fund targeting socially responsible small and medium-sized enterprises;
- Den Sociale Kapitalfond Effekt: Investment fund for public-private partnerships that create positive social outcomes;
- The commercial foundation, Den Sociale Kapitalfond: Laboratory and think tank for social impact investments.

Established in 2011 by Lars Jannick Johansen and TrygFonden, Den Sociale Kapitalfond is a Scandinavian pioneer in social impact investments.

Dubai Green Fund is a Dubai Government impact investment organization anchored by Dubai Electricity & Water Authority “DEWA”. DGF invests and finances projects and companies that are engaged in environmentally supportive activities such as: 

	Clean Energy Production;
	Energy & Water Efficiency;
	Green Transportation & Logistics;
	Sustainable Living;
	Water and waste management; 
	Sustainable Agriculture
	Green Real Estate

“The Dubai Green Fund was launched by His Highness Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid Al Maktoum, Vice President and Prime Minister of the UAE and Ruler of Dubai, to encourage investment in green projects and foster Dubai’s position as a global hub for the green economy.”

H.E. Saeed Mohammed Al Tayer, Chairman of Dubai Green Fund and MD & CEO of DEWA

O NOSSO MELHOR PARA O SEU MELHOR

Nós somos o Grupo Gondaski!

A holding que detém empresas especializadas em diferentes áreas. Com sede em Ponta Grossa (PR) contamos com mais de 500 colaboradores em mais de 19 pontos de operações nos estados do Paraná, São Paulo, Mato Grosso e Tocantins, com as empresas:

MacPonta Agro - Concessionária John Deere para máquinas, peças, serviços e tecnologia agrícola;

MacPonta Caminhões - Concessionária DAF para caminhões e pós-vendas;

MacPonta Rental - Locação de veículos para empresas;

MacPonta Corretora de Seguros - Especializada em seguros agrícolas, riscos operacionais em negócios, aeronaves e pessoas;

 S&G Agricultura - Produção de grãos e operações agrícolas;

Insight Wave - Empresa de tecnologia e inteligência analítica.

Somos uma das mil maiores empresas do Brasil, de acordo com o ranking Valor 1000, da revista Valor Econômico. E, também estamos no ranking da Great Place To Work (GPTW), entre as melhores empresas para se trabalhar do Paraná, uma das certificações mais importantes no que se refere à gestão de pessoas.

Aqui ouvimos, desenvolvemos e reconhecemos as pessoas de forma genuína. Cada um de nós assume a responsabilidade pelo que é devido e nos comprometemos a entregar o melhor com qualidade e excelência. Não nos conformamos em fazer apenas o necessário.

Trabalhamos todos os dias com um propósito em comum para nossos colaboradores, clientes e a comunidade: fazer o nosso melhor para a vida prosperar.

LEVERAGING OPERATING PERFORMANCE & INTERNATIONAL EXPANSION

Nexxus Iberia Fund I plans to invest in 8 to 10 small to medium sized companies in Spain and generate compelling returns for investors. The Fund will make individual investments of typically €10 million to €25 million of equity through flexible majority and minority financing solutions.

What Nexxus Iberia focuses on is finding the right management and companies to fuel the underlying business growth, rather than burdening portfolio companies with high levels of debt.

Nexxus Iberia Partners have proven experience delivering portfolio companies' growth through:
- Operational improvements;
- International expansion, mainly to Europe and LatAm;
- Sourcing top managers and advisors;
- Acquisitions and the development of new businesses;
- Adoption of technology and digital strategies.

Private Capital Belgium  is the professional association representing the venture capital (VC) and private equity (PE) community in Belgium. Our members are investment fund managers and professionals who deliver services to the community. 

Main goals of the association are :

- to foster active networking amongst our members and between our members and third parties;
- to be the industry’s recognized spokesperson and to be the collective voice towards various authorities, regulatory bodies, and other stakeholders;
- to improve the quality of the operation of the industry; to contribute to the training of qualified managerial groups both in funds and in their portfolio companies; and, to spread an appropriate culture;
- to contribute to the continuous development of business in our industry by promoting the adoption of legislative and/or regulatory developments that facilitate investment activities; to promote a climate of entrepreneurship and lasting added-value creation; and, to stimulate innovation;
- to collect and analyse socio-economic, financial, legal and fiscal data related to the industry and to provide extensive information to its members, policy makers, academics and other bodies on all relevant topics;
- to ensure contacts with similar associations in Belgium and abroad (Invest Europe, other national Venture Capital Associations).

Azur Innovation Fund est un fonds d'amorçage qui vise la maximisation de valeur pour l’ensemble des parties prenantes des projets financés: actionnaires, promoteurs, salariés, écosystème industriel, collectivités ...

Pour ce faire, Azur Innovation a mobilisé (i) des Investisseurs de premier plan tant nationaux qu’internationaux (ii) 
des compétences du capital amorçage (iii) des professionnels reconnus de le domaine de l’accompagnement.

Azur Innovation est centré sur une approche smart capital qui associe au financement, le mentorat, le coaching, l’assistance technique et le monitoring.

Ainsi,  AZUR INNOVATION apporte :
- des investisseurs de référence ;
- de l’expertise et de l’expérience en matière de structuration et de déploiement des business model, de pilotage et restructuration de montage et de mise en œuvre de schémas financiers complexes de cessions à des industriels ou d’éventuelles introductions en bourse ;
- des procédures et des critères rigoureux de monitoring, de contrôle interne et fine tuning des Business Model ;
- un cadre de gouvernance ;
- des systèmes de gestion des impacts sociaux et environnementaux ;
- une capacité d’endettement ;
- un appui pour les futures levées de fonds.

Golden Egg Check is a (pre-)Seed venture capital fund with a focus on the Netherlands and Europa. We connect founders and investors, collect data about the venture capital ecosystem and give fundraising training for startups.

With years of experience studying VC' investment preferences and decision-making processes, we employ their best practices to strategically invest and enable our customers to select tomorrow’s winners.

In short we:
- invest in startups and scaleups together with great angels and VC funds;
- connect startups with relevant VCs and angel investors (eg. via StartupRoulette or direct introductions)
- help investors to find promising companies before others do;
- assist corporates to find and select companies that fit a strategy or challenge;
- run the most extensive startup funding database in the Netherlands. 

More info at www.goldeneggcheck.com and https://startuproulette.nl/
